<item>
            <title>[LU-9105] Unknown config parameter in llog fails mounting target</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-9105</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;If we have unknown config parameter in llog then it fails the target mounting.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Able to re-create it easily with following steps:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;$&amp;gt;sh llmount.sh&lt;br/&gt;
$&amp;gt;export NOFORMAT=yes&lt;br/&gt;
$&amp;gt;for OST in $(lctl get_param mgs.MGS.live.lustre | grep OST); do echo &quot;max_rpcs_in_flight=50 on $OST&quot; ; lctl conf_param $OST.ost.max_rpcs_in_flight=50 ; done &amp;lt;--- Note here ost.max.. is mention instead of osc.max..&lt;br/&gt;
$&amp;gt;sh llmountcleanup.sh&lt;br/&gt;
$&amp;gt;sh llmount.sh &amp;lt;------- this hangs&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
